ztlp-ebpf (C / eBPF Packet Filter)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

eBPF programs interact with the Linux kernel via the BPF syscall interface.
Linux kernel BPF headers are licensed under GPL-2.0 with the Linux syscall
exception (SPDX: Linux-syscall-note), which permits user-space programs
(including eBPF programs loaded via bpf()) to use these headers without
triggering GPL obligations on the user-space code. This interpretation is
consistent with industry practice (Cilium, Cloudflare, Meta) and the
kernel's UAPI header licensing.

The ztlp-ebpf user-space loader and eBPF programs themselves are licensed
under Apache License 2.0.

No third-party C libraries used. ✓

